<p><FONT size=5 face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" color="#334455"><b><u>Zone Guides.</u></b></FONT><p><ul><FONT size=3 face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" color="#8b1a1a"><p align="center">Sol A = Tinkers bag in a day... By Broca Faultline of E'ci</p>
<p>And I will tell you how.  I'm writing this from the perspective of level 51 with 201 bandage skill.  Lower levels can attempt this, but you may not be quite as successful.  I'm also assuming you have a haste item of some sort, and are decently equipped otherwise.  You should also have decent faction with the gnomes in Sol A, if yours sucks, go to Sol B and kill some kobolds and fire giants.  Preferably you can get your Magic Resist to at least 50.  Also you should have some pumice.  You should also know how to feign casting mobs, and if you don't know how to do this by now, then please go back to playing your Druid. (/ooc I always blame druids when I see a twink of any class with no skills, even though it could be any class.  Sorry if I offend any of the decent druids out there).  You should know your way around Sol A.  It doesn't have to be perfect, but you have to be able to get from entrance to the gnome area, and then to the bartender area.  Now on with the farming...
  NO one can farm Sol A like a monk.  A shadowknight would be a close second, but their feign just isn't good enough.</p><p>Starting at the entrance, here is my routine when I come into Sol A.  I run in, and cross the bridge heading towards the gnomes.  Just across the bridge there are 2 low level goblins and I usually hit FD just after I pass them.  If I don't fail my feign or have it broke by some caster, I get right back up and keep running.  Run all the way to the end of the hall, and kill the Kobold Predator or his Placeholder.  He's the one at the end of the hall, if you're not sure, he wanders a real short path, just feign and wait for him.</p><p>You're right next to the Foreman now, so go into his room.  His room is the one with the well in it.  Entering from the Predator side, the placeholder for the Foreman is the one across the well from you.  Kill him, ignore the greenies beating on you, and run back to where the Kobold Predator was and feign.  He is the only wanderer right here, so as soon as the goblins leave, you can stop a few seconds and bandage up.</p><p>All bandaged and good to go?  Head to where Kindle spawns.  I usually enter at the 5 on <a href="http://monks.volitionx.com/soluseka.htm">Jekhar's map</a> Run in past all the goblins, hug the left side and feign where you don't see a spawn.  Lay here for a bit.  There are 2 ways to do this part.  You can wait until you see a wandering goblin, pop up and kill it, or you can just kill all the goblins you see in a 1 mile radius.  I usually prefer the first option, as I have tried the second option a few times, and I never feel positive I got Kindle's placeholder.  It should only take a few minutes, just be patient, pretend it's Raster or something, it'll feel like a short wait then.</p><p>After you kill Kindle or the wanderer, head towards the goblin Captain.  I just open the door and bum rush him.  He's fairly easy to kill/loot/feign.</p><p>Wait for the mobs to leave, and then run out of the Captain's room and take the door on your left.  Follow this hall until you fall down a pit.  Be ready to feign.  You did bring pumice, didn't you?  In the back of this pit you're in, there is the place holder for the Reckless Efreeti, there is also 2 blazing elementals here.  Dispel his damage sheild, kill him, take his armband, and then run out and bring the elementals with you.</p><p>Now one of the coolest things in Sol A is that the goblins and blazing elementals don't like each other.  When you run out of here (through the hidden wall opposite where the Efreeti was) make a left and go through the door.  Head towards the gnomes.  The first goblins you see, wait for the Elementals to get there, and feign.  The Elementals will fight the goblin and hopefully win.  Usually when I'm here, I use the Elementals to kill as many goblins as I can.  The record I've had them kill is 5.  The shamans and wizard goblins really put the hurt on my poor pet Elementals.  Then I run to the gnomes.</p><p>If you see a gnome standing in the middle of the path, wait a few seconds and see if it wanders.  If it does, KEEEL IT!  That's the Model Exg's Place holder.</p><p>Then run to Gabbie.  If she's up, get out your pumice.  Make sure you put on all your Magic resist gear.  Might even want to wait for mend to load up if it's not already.  She's a wizard and can do a lot of damage fast.  After Gabby, bandage back up, and head to the Lava Elemental.  If you already have a Runed Lava Pendant, go anyway =).</p><p>In his room, there is only 1 wanderer, kill the wanderer.  If the Lava Elemental is up when you get there, check to see if he has a damage shield up.  If not, keel it, if he does, dispel him.  If you don't have pumice, here is the tactic I used before I got my tranquil staff (now I just kill it :P).  I kick him then if I get burned, I feign.  Wait for Feign and Flying Kick to reload, then pop up and kick him again until the duration on the damage shield wears off.  If he drops the runed lava pendant, take the one off your neck and go find an out of the way gnome somewhere and give the pendant to him.  Go back and get the pendant off the elemental.  Call all of your friends (or get an alt there) and either give them your lava pendant, or have them kill the gnome who is holding the extra.</p><p>Now run back to the Kobold Predator and repeat the cycle.  After you get good at this, you can farm almost all the named spawns in Sol A.  At level 53 with dragon haste and a Jade mace/fist combo, I was able to camp all the above spawns as well as Singe (I wouldn't suggest killing him as his PH is also a wanderer and finding and killing it can waste valuable time), the Goblin King, bartender, torturer, high shaman, drunkard.  I'd miss the kobold predator's spawn time by about 2 minutes.  Now I have a fungal tunic and a tranquil staff, I bet I can do them all and have time to spare.  Best loot to date, I had Sol A all to myself for 6 hours.  I left the place with 2 plat armbands, 3 kobold hide boots, obsidian shard, foreman tunic, obsidian bead hoop, 2 pairs imp skins, 1 runed lava pendant, charred boots, guants, 2 charred guardian shields, charred guardian BP, 1 drake hide legs, and a turquoise eyepatch.  Roughly 15k for 8 hours of play time.  I ended up giving it all away to guild mates after I got what I needed out of the cash, but it was still a real good day.</p><p>Good luck to you all.</p></FONT>

</td>
